1

00:00:00,000  -->  00:00:02,080
Next up in our hierarchy of exceptions,

2

00:00:02,080  -->  00:00:03,800
we have keyboard interrupt.

3

00:00:03,800  -->  00:00:08,380
Picture yourself in the theme park and suddenly you hit an emergency stop button.

4

00:00:08,380  -->  00:00:12,340
Keyboard interrupt is raised when a user manually interrupts the program,

5

00:00:12,340  -->  00:00:15,440
usually by pressing control C. It's handy

6

00:00:15,440  -->  00:00:19,120
for halting a running script when you need to stop immediately.

7

00:00:19,120  -->  00:00:23,440
Imagine you need to stop a ride from going further or to close a ride.

8

00:00:23,440  -->  00:00:27,080
There are many times where a user's input could be necessary,

9

00:00:27,080  -->  00:00:32,340
and we'd want Python to handle the rest for us after a human initiates a stop sequence.

10

00:00:32,340  -->  00:00:36,205
This one will also be a bit easier to see in an example.

11

00:00:36,205  -->  00:00:38,405
Let's dive into one right now.

12

00:00:38,405  -->  00:00:40,830
Let's talk about keyboard interrupt.

13

00:00:40,830  -->  00:00:44,790
For your theme park, let's say that the rides need to have a switch to

14

00:00:44,790  -->  00:00:49,230
turn them on and also have a human override to stop them at any time.

15

00:00:49,230  -->  00:00:52,210
We'll create a run theme park ride function,

16

00:00:52,210  -->  00:00:53,570
and once it's running,

17

00:00:53,570  -->  00:00:56,430
it will need a user input to write stop.

18

00:00:56,430  -->  00:00:58,650
If a user does write stop,

19

00:00:58,650  -->  00:01:02,010
then this raises a keyboard interrupt exception,

20

00:01:02,010  -->  00:01:06,760
and then this will shut down the ride our code from running.

21

00:01:06,760  -->  00:01:12,605
Let's write an example of this function and see this exception in action.

22

00:01:12,605  -->  00:01:15,540
We will define this function, we'll say define,

23

00:01:15,540  -->  00:01:19,140
def run, theme park, ride,

24

00:01:19,140  -->  00:01:21,800
then we'll do tr for a tri case,

25

00:01:21,800  -->  00:01:24,000
and we'll say,

26

00:01:24,000  -->  00:01:27,820
this is true, user input equals input.

27

00:01:27,820  -->  00:01:33,460
We'll say type, stop to stop the ride colon space,

28

00:01:33,460  -->  00:01:34,955
and then we'll do quotes.

29

00:01:34,955  -->  00:01:38,365
Then we'll close out that parenthesis for the input.

30

00:01:38,365  -->  00:01:42,040
Then we'll say if g user input dot

31

00:01:42,040  -->  00:01:46,780
lower because we want to convert it into lower case equals, stop.

32

00:01:46,780  -->  00:01:49,115
It's not case specific.

33

00:01:49,115  -->  00:01:52,860
Then we'll raise a keyboard interrupt.

34

00:01:52,860  -->  00:01:54,960
We'll go back to the same level of try.

35

00:01:54,960  -->  00:01:56,480
We'll now write our except case,

36

00:01:56,480  -->  00:01:59,980
and we'll say except, keyboard interrupt.

37

00:01:59,980  -->  00:02:03,260
Then we'll say, Colin here, we'll say print,

38

00:02:03,260  -->  00:02:09,795
say you interrupted and stopped the ride. Close out that print statement.

39

00:02:09,795  -->  00:02:12,980
Then, if we were to run this function,

40

00:02:12,980  -->  00:02:15,760
can you guess what the output is going to look like?

41

00:02:15,760  -->  00:02:17,560
Let's run this code and find out.

42

00:02:17,560  -->  00:02:20,160
When we run this, we'll see an input field,

43

00:02:20,160  -->  00:02:22,830
and it'll say type stop to stop the ride.

44

00:02:22,830  -->  00:02:25,620
Inside this box, we will need to write the word

45

00:02:25,620  -->  00:02:29,740
stop to end this ride and stop our code from running.

46

00:02:29,740  -->  00:02:33,960
Will continue to stay running and continuously prompt you for an input.

47

00:02:33,960  -->  00:02:35,780
If we were to type stop,

48

00:02:35,780  -->  00:02:38,540
this raises a keyboard exception,

49

00:02:38,540  -->  00:02:44,200
which then causes us to execute an end to the function.

50

00:02:44,200  -->  00:02:47,060
This stops the program and then triggers the accept block,

51

00:02:47,060  -->  00:02:48,910
which is why we see this print statement here.

52

00:02:48,910  -->  00:02:50,960
It says, you interrupted and stop the ride,

53

00:02:50,960  -->  00:02:52,340
which is why we see that here.

54

00:02:52,340  -->  00:02:54,380
Otherwise, the code will keep running,

55

00:02:54,380  -->  00:03:00,700
or should I say our theme park ride continuing to operate as expected?
